<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,307,1479,1505]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Parexothrips</emphasis>
Priesner
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,1550,1682]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
This genus was redefined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bhatti" box="[485,638,1550,1574]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refString="Bhatti, J. S. (1975) A revision of Exothrips Priesner and two related genera. Oriental Insects, 9, 43 - 90." type="journal article" year="1975">
Bhatti (
<number box="[570,630,1550,1574]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="1975.0">1975</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, who distinguished it from 
<taxonomicName box="[953,1062,1550,1574]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Exothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[953,1062,1550,1574]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Exothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and described a second species. The two genera share most character states, but in 
<taxonomicName box="[718,863,1587,1611]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Parexothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[718,863,1587,1611]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Parexothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species ocellar setae pair III arise outside the ocellar triangle, the prosternal basantra bears two or more pairs of setae, and the prosternal ferna is incomplete medially.
</paragraph>
